'''= The sharing of experiences or thoughts usually considered private. Coined to suggest an opposition to "intimacy."'''


=Description=

"it was coined the French psychiatrist Jacques Lacan (1901-1981), who called it extimité. For Lacan and his followers, extimacy expressed "the opposition between inside and outside, between container and contained." 
